    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-07-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="492"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Choate</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-07-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>British embassy advises me, in answer to an inquiry, that the governor of Bermuda
                    has not yet received instructions as to how the Boer prisoners are to be dealt
                    with. You will inquire when and how any American citizens held as prisoners will
                    be released, and suggest that instructions be sent by cable to Bermuda.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
